		<header class="story-header">
		<h1 itemprop="headline" class="story-heading entry-title"><span>A Sweet Forgetting: Slavery, Sugar and Scotland</span></h1>		<div class="story-meta entry-meta">
			<span class="author vcard byline-author"
					itemscope=""
					itemprop="author creator"
					itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
					By <span class="fn" itemprop="name">Fayemi Shakur</span>
				</span><!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2015-10-07T07:00:19+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">Oct. 7, 2015</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">Oct. 7, 2015</span><span class="postMetaHeaderCommentCount commentCount hidden">
					<i class="icon"></i>
					<a class="commentCountLink commentCountNumberOnly" href="//lens.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/10/07/stephen-mclaren-jamaica-sugar-scotland-caribbean/"></a>
				</span>		</div>
	</header>
	<div class="shareTools sharetools layout-vertical" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//lens.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/10/07/stephen-mclaren-jamaica-sugar-scotland-caribbean/" data-title="A Sweet Forgetting: Slavery, Sugar and Scotland" data-description="A Scottish-born photographer was drawn to Jamaica to explore how his homelandâs wealth was built on the backs of slave labor in the Caribbean."><div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div></div>	<div class="post-content">
				<script>
			if ( window.innerWidth < 975 ) {
